@dev Event for logging a call event for the extended contract.
 @notice | All of the logs below are *only for debug & further development purposes* - The "system" cannot
         | currently output event logs, but these will work fine for truffle testing purposes.

@param _administratorAddress The new Administrator address for the extended functions.
 @dev | Sets the Administrator address for the extended functions:
      | i. remove: removal of administrator access permanently.
      | ii. rewards: set whether rewards should be given to the extended contract
      | iii. calls: set whether an extended call sequence should be given to the extended contract
      | iii. the smart contract address of the extended contract to distribute to
 @return result
    | true = administrator set
    | false = administrator already set

@dev Removes of administrator access permanently.
 @return result
    | true = administrator permanently removed
    | false = not administrator

@param _exRewardsEnabled Whether the extended contract rewards should be enabled.
 @dev Sets whether rewards should be given to the extended contract (block rewards)
 @return result
    | true = ex rewards set
    | false = not administrator

@param _exCallsEnabled Whether an extended call sequence should be given to the extended contract.
 @dev | Sets whether an extended call sequence should be given to the extended contract. These calls are
      | explicitly called by the system itself, which currently does *not* propagate any events to the system.
 @notice | Enabling these calls without proper audit and due diligence can result in the entire block reward contract
         | being disabled, so measures exist to halt this within this contract (if not explicitly disabled), set up a new receiver contract connection, and then re-enabled system features.
 @return result
    | true = ex calls set
    | false = not administrator

@param _exContractAddress The new extended contract address for block rewards & potential calls (if enabled)
 @dev Sets the smart contract address of the extended contract to distribute to
 @return result
    | true = ex contract address set
    | false = not administrator

@param _benefactorAddress The benefactor addresses that will be consistently referenced (the administration key of the block author/sealer).
 @param _delegateAddress The Delegate address that will now determine on-chain administrative concerns (setting a benefactor's Coinbase, etc.)
 @dev Sets the Benefactor's Delegate (administration proxy). This is initially set by the benefactor's keys, and allows the delegate control over the Coinbase (reward) address for this benefactor (block sealer).
 @return result
    | 3 = set benefactor's delegate
    | 2 = delegate is already assigned to a benefactor
    | 1 = benefactor not recognized as a sealer, so no action taken.
    | 0 = message sender not able to set benefactor's coinbase

@param _benefactorAddress The benefactor addresses that will be consistently referenced (the administration key of the block author/sealer).
 @param _coinbaseAddress The Coinbase (reward destination) address from Shyft tokens from the inflation, as equivalent barter payment for node services ex. uptime.
 @dev Sets the Benefactor's Coinbase (reward destination). This is either set by the benefactor (block author) initially, or by the benefactor's administration delegate.
 @return result
    | 1 = set benefactor's coinbase
    | 0 = message sender not able to set benefactor's coinbase

@param _benefactorAddress The benefactor addresses that will be consistently referenced (the administration key of the block author/sealer).
 @dev Gets the Benefactor's Delegate (administration proxy).
 @return result the benefactor's delegate.

@param _benefactorAddress The benefactor addresses that will be consistently referenced (the administration key of the block author/sealer).
 @dev Gets the Benefactor's Coinbase (administration proxy).
 @return result the benefactor's coinbase

@param _delegateAddress The delegate addresses.
 @dev Gets the Delegate's original Benefactor address.
 @return result the delegate's original benefactor address.

@param _blockSealerAddress The block sealer's address.
 @dev Gets whether a specific block Sealer has ever sealed a block.
 @return result whether the block sealer has ever sealed a block

@param _blockSealerAddress The block sealer's address.
 @dev Gets the last time a specific block Sealer has sealed a block.
 @return result the last time the block sealer has ever sealed a block
